# 200-compose-ui.mdc
# Applies to: **/*Screen.kt, **/*Composable.kt

You are building Jetpack Compose UI for Mini Cuadre Caja, an ERP/POS app used in real business operations.

==================================================
PRIMARY GOAL
==================================================

Design UI for:

- speed
- clarity
- low error rate
- touch efficiency
- readability
- reliability under pressure

Beauty is secondary to operational efficiency.

==================================================
UI PHILOSOPHY
==================================================

This is not a social app.

Users may be:
- cashier in rush hour
- admin reviewing numbers
- staff using low-end devices
- users with little technical training

Therefore UI must be:

- obvious
- fast
- forgiving
- legible
- stable

==================================================
GENERAL COMPOSE RULES
==================================================

- Prefer small reusable composables.
- Keep screens readable.
- Hoist state upward.
- Stateless composables when possible.
- Use Material 3 components.
- Keep previews useful when practical.

Avoid deeply nested UI trees.

==================================================
SCREEN STRUCTURE
==================================================

Prefer layout:

Scaffold
- TopBar
- Content
- Bottom actions / FAB if useful
- SnackbarHost

Use consistent sections:

- Header summary
- Main actions
- Data list/table
- Secondary actions

==================================================
VISUAL PRIORITIES
==================================================

Numbers and actions matter most.

Emphasize:

- totals
- pending sync
- warnings
- close shift actions
- payment method choices

De-emphasize decorative elements.

==================================================
SPACING + READABILITY
==================================================

Use consistent spacing.

Prefer:
- 8dp minor gaps
- 16dp standard padding
- 24dp section separation

Avoid cramped layouts.

==================================================
TYPOGRAPHY
==================================================

Use hierarchy clearly:

- Large: totals / balances / titles
- Medium: labels / cards
- Small: metadata / timestamps

Never make critical numbers tiny.

==================================================
COLOR USAGE
==================================================

Use color semantically:

Positive:
- success
- synced
- confirmed

Warning:
- pending
- mismatch
- caution

Critical:
- closure difference
- failed sync
- blocking errors

Do not rely only on color; add text/icon.

==================================================
BUTTON RULES
==================================================

Primary actions must be obvious.

Examples:
- Registrar Venta
- Cerrar Caja
- Sincronizar
- Confirmar

Dangerous actions need confirmation.

Buttons should be large enough for touch use.

Avoid tiny icon-only critical actions.

==================================================
FORM RULES
==================================================

For data entry:

- Use numeric keyboard where needed
- Auto focus when useful
- Clear labels
- Inline validation
- Preserve entered values on recomposition

Prefer fewer fields.

==================================================
LISTS / TABLES
==================================================

Use LazyColumn for large lists.

Rows should expose quickly:

- item name
- amount
- status
- timestamp
- quick action if needed

Use sticky headers if useful.

==================================================
CASHIER UX RULES
==================================================

Optimize repetitive flows:

- minimum taps
- large touch targets
- category shortcuts
- clear totals always visible
- fast return after action

If user sells 100 times/day, save taps.

==================================================
ERROR STATES
==================================================

Always design states for:

- loading
- empty
- offline
- retry
- validation error
- server failure

Do not leave blank screens.

==================================================
SYNC STATUS UX
==================================================

Show clearly:

- Synced
- Pending
- Retrying
- Failed

User must trust data state.

==================================================
FINANCIAL UI RULES
==================================================

Money formatting must be consistent.

Always show currency clearly.

Examples:
$12,500

Highlight:
- expected cash
- counted cash
- difference
- transfers
- expenses

==================================================
DIALOGS
==================================================

Use dialogs only for:

- confirmations
- blocking warnings
- critical differences
- delete/cancel actions

Avoid dialog abuse.

==================================================
RESPONSIVE RULES
==================================================

Support:

- phones
- tablets
- desktop future scaling

Use adaptive layouts when sensible.

Avoid hardcoded sizes tied to one device.

==================================================
PERFORMANCE RULES
==================================================

- Avoid heavy recomposition
- Use remember when appropriate
- Stable parameters preferred
- Avoid expensive formatting each frame

==================================================
ACCESSIBILITY
==================================================

- Touch targets large enough
- Text readable
- Content descriptions where useful
- Contrast acceptable

==================================================
ANTI-PATTERNS TO AVOID
==================================================

- Overdesigned dashboards with poor usability
- Tiny text for totals
- Hidden critical actions
- Too many colors
- Long forms for quick tasks
- Multiple competing buttons
- Empty states with no guidance

==================================================
WHEN ASKED TO BUILD A SCREEN
==================================================

Prioritize:

1. User task flow
2. Speed
3. Error prevention
4. Clear state handling
5. Clean visuals

==================================================
FINAL PRIORITY ORDER
==================================================

1. Operational speed
2. Accuracy
3. Clarity
4. Reliability
5. Visual polish